==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*funsti-'', from Indo-European ''*pnsti-'', a variant of ''*pnksti-'' ‘fist’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[fest]] (Frisian [[fest]]), Old Saxon [[fust|fūst]] (Dutch [[vuist]]), Old High German [[fust|fūst]] (German [[Faust]]), and with Russian [[пясть]] ‘palm of the hand’, Polish [[pięść]] ‘fist’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fy:st/

===Noun===
'''fȳst''' ''f''
# the [[fist]]


